<h4 id="1-idea">1. Idea</h4>
<p>Every integral evolves:</p>
<ul>
  <li>a path</li>
  <li>a covector field(differential form)</li>
</ul>

<h4 id="2-example-single-variable">2. Example: single variable</h4>

\[\int_{0}^{2}(-6 x+4) d x
=\int_{0}^{2} \frac{d F}{d x} d x
= \int_{0}^{2} d F\]

\[\begin{array}{l}\frac{d F}{d x}=-6 x+4 \\ F(x)=-3 x^{2}+4 x+c\end{array}\]

<h4 id="2-example-two-variables">2. Example: two variables</h4>

\[\int_{P} y d x+x d y\]

\[\begin{array}{l}\int_{P} d F \quad d F=\frac{\partial F}{\partial x} d
x+\frac{\partial F}{\partial y} d y \\ =\int_{P} \frac{\partial F}{\partial x} d
x+\frac{\partial F}{\partial y} d y\end{array}\]

